Bank of Japan Adds 3 Trillion Yen to Financial System in One-Day Operation

-- B y   N a o t o   H o s o d a
-- 
2011-03-18T00:06:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-18/bank-of-japan-adds-37-billion-to-financial-system-to-help-boost-liquidity.html
The  Bank of Japan (8301)  added 3 trillion
yen ($37 billion) to the financial system in a one-day
operation, bringing the total of emergency fund injections this
week to 37 trillion yen.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Naoto Hosoda at 
